<p>Other types of balls and game twists are introduced as the levels progress. Some examples are fast balls,
    shielded
    balls, slow-mo balls, death balls, and trapped balls. The fast balls travel faster than normal, and slo-mo
    balls
    slow down time. The shielded balls have a shell around them that has to broken off by contacting the paddle
    several
    times. The death balls end the game if they contact the paddle, but they move very slow. Lastly, the trapped
    balls
    are stuck in place until the player shoots them with a projectile that is released from the paddle. </p>

